Security at the Champions League final has been slammed as "shambolic" after reports claimed ticketless fans had made their way into the stadium. Liverpool will take on Real Madrid at the Stade de France on Saturday night, but it seems some Reds supporters have been unable to get into the ground. Pundits and journalists attempting to make their way into the Stade de France for the Champions League final reported chaotic scenes at security gates with reports suggesting ticketless fans had managed to make their way into the stadium. Sky Sports pundit Kelly Cates tweeted: "Absolutely shambolic at the Stade de France. No way in, no way of knowing which way to go. Stay safe if youâ€™re heading in It has the potential to be very dangerous." French outlet RMC Sport claimed that "hundreds" of fans had managed to get past security and into the stadium despite not having tickets for the match. Liverpool fans were reportedly forced to wait in massive queues outside the ground while security struggled to get them into the ground. **We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures, and video on this breaking news story. For the latest news and breaking news visit:/sport/football Stay up to date with all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion, and video on the stories that matter to you. Follow us on Twitter @DExpress_Sport - the official Daily Express & Express.co.uk Twitter account - providing real news in real-time. We're also on Facebook @DailyExpressSport - offering your must-see news, features, videos, and pictures throughout the day to like, comment, and share from the Daily Express, Sunday Express, and Express.co.uk.**